recall(s): [{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'10V002000', u'Conequence': u'IN THE EVENT OF A CRASH RESULTING IN SIDE CURTAIN AIR BAG DEPLOYMENT, THE TRIM PIECE MAY NOT REMAIN PROPERLY SECURED TO THE A-PILLAR, INCREASING THE RISK OF INJURY TO THE DRIVER AND/OR FRONT SEAT PASSENGER.', u'Notes': u"OWNERS MAY ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S VEHICLE SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), OR GO TO HTTP://WWW.SAFERCAR.GOV .", u'Component': u'AIR BAGS', u'Summary': u"HONDA IS RECALLING CERTAIN MODEL YEAR ACURA 2010 MDX VEHICLES MANUFACTURED BETWEEN OCTOBER 7, 2009 AND NOVEMBER 14, 2009. ", u'Remedy': u'DEALERS WILL INSPECT THE INTERIOR TRIM PIECE OF THE A-PILLAR AND IF A BOLT IS MISSING IT WILL BE INSTALLED FREE OF CHARGE. [{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'13V114000', u'Conequence': u"Failure to illuminate the stop lamps during braking or inability to disengage the cruise control could increase the risk of a crash. ", u'Notes': u'Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov. ', u'Component': u'EXTERIOR LIGHTING:BRAKE LIGHTS:SWITCH | SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC:SWITCHES:BRAKE LIGHT', u'Summary': u'Kia Motors Corporation (Kia) is recalling certain model year 2007-2010 Rondo, model year 2007-2011 Sedona, Sorento and Sportage, model year 2010-2011 Soul, model year 2008-2011 Optima, model year 2010 Forte, model year 2007-2009 Amanti, and model year 2009 Borrego vehicles.  Originally, in April 2013, Kia recalled 623,658 model year 2007-2010 Rondo and Sportage, model year 2007-2011 Sorento, model year 2007 Sedona, model year 2010-2011 Soul, and model year 2011 Optima vehicles.   In September 2013, Kia informed the agency that it was adding an additional 356,719 vehicles to this campaign.  The total number of vehicles being recalled is now 980,377.  In the affected vehicles, the stop lamp switch may malfunction.  A malfunctioning stop lamp switch may cause the brake lights to not illuminate when the brake pedal is depressed or may cause an inability to deactivate the cruise control by depressing the brake pedal.  Additionally, a malfunctioning stop lamp switch may also result in intermittent operation of the push-button start feature, affect the operation of the brake-transmission shift interlock feature preventing the shifter from being moved out of the PARK position and cause the Electronic Stability Control (ESC) malfunction light to illuminate.', u'Remedy': u"Kia will send an interim notification to owners in May 2013. Owners may contact Kia customer service at 1-800-333-4542.  Kia's number for this recall is SC165.

", u'Summary': u'Kia Motors America (Kia) is recalling certain 2010-2013 Kia Forte, Forte Koup, 2011-2013 Kia Optima and 2011-2012 Kia Optima Hybrid and Sedona vehicles. [{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'12V460000', u'Conequence': u"If the tabs were to fracture and separate, the shift lever and the actual position of the transmission gear may not match. The vehicle may not be able to be restarted and the vehicle could roll away after the driver has exited the vehicle, resulting in a possible crash without prior warning.", u'Notes': u"General Motors safety recall number 12106. ', u'Remedy': u'GM will notify owners, and dealers will install a retainer over the cable end or replace the shift cable as necessary. This service will be performed free of charge. ', u'ModelYear': u'2010', u'Model': u'G6', u'Make': u'PONTIAC', u'ReportReceivedDate': u'/Date(1405915200000-0400)/', u'Manufacturer': u'Dorman Products, Inc.'}, {u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'14V252000', u'Conequence': u'Any of the above failure conditions increases the risk of a crash.', u'Notes': u'Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.', u'Component': u'ELECTRICAL SYSTEM:WIRING | ELECTRONIC STABILITY CONTROL | EXTERIOR LIGHTING:BRAKE LIGHTS | SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC:SWITCHES:BRAKE LIGHT | VEHICLE SPEED CONTROL:CRUISE CONTROL', u'Remedy': u"GM will notify owners, and dealers will attach the wiring harness to the BCM with a spacer, apply dielectric lubricant to both the BCM and harness connector and the BAS and harness connector, and will relearn the brake pedal home position, free of charge. GM's number for this recall is 13036.", u'Summary': u"General Motors LLC (GM) is recalling certain model year 2004-2012 Chevrolet Malibu vehicles manufactured May 16, 2003, through October 11, 2012, 2004-2007 Malibu Maxx vehicles manufactured June 25, 2003, through April 5, 2007, 2005-2010 Pontiac G6 vehicles manufactured May 26, 2004, through January 4, 2010, and 2007-2010 Saturn Aura vehicles manufactured April 24, 2006, through May 26, 2009.  In the affected vehicles, increased resistance in the Body Control Module (BCM) connection may result in voltage fluctuations in the Brake Apply Sensor (BAS) circuit. ", u'Component': u'POWER TRAIN:AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION', u'Remedy': u'VOLKSWAGEN WILL REPROGRAM THE TRANSMISSION CONTROL MODULE WITH UPDATED SOFTWARE FREE OF CHARGE.
